description: The quest that led to Infinity Gauntlet begins here! Back from the dead, Thanos is after the power to bring the rest of the universe with him on a return trip! Can the Silver Surfer, Drax the Destroyer and others stop the cosmic iconoclast before he uses reality as a token of his affection for Death? Special guest-appearance by the Impossible Man! Collecting SILVER SURFER (1987) #34-38, THANOS QUEST #1-2 and material from LOGAN'S RUN #6.
name: Silver Surfer: Rebirth of Thanos

description:
As Ganta begins to understand his new disturbing power, he becomes more determined to destroy the Red Man. However, his strange abilities prove to be an obstacle to Chief Makina who is resolute in maintaining peace and order in her territory. With conspiracy and monstrous attacks from every angle, Ganta manages to arrive at Ward G, a mysterious, detached location in Deadman Wonderland where the horrendous bloodbath continues...

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 5: Necro Macro
  • Chapter 6: Crow Craw
  • Chapter 7: Carnival of Corpses
  • Chapter 8: Bloodthirsty Majesty
name: Vol. 2

description: Batman and Superman travel to an uncharted island in the Caribbean in an attempt to stop the evil Professor Combs from performing a Voodoo ritual that will turn the living into the undead. But when vampires and werewolves get involved, The Dark Knight will find himself six feet under and buried alive!
name: Batman vs The Undead Part Four: The Corpses of Corto Maltese

description: Spinning out of ASTONISHING X-MEN comes a story that will take you places youve never been! After Secret Invasion, Agent Brand is no longer the top dog at S.W.O.R.D. Forced to share her leadership post with former Avengers-liaison Henry Gyrich, Brand is less than pleased. Will the arrival of her boyfriend, X-Man Beast, help her out? Not when she discovers Gyrichs plan for fixing S.W.O.R.D. is to rid Earth of ALL ALIENS! Brought to you by Kieron Gillen (DARK AVENGERS: ARES), Steven Sanders (Five Fists of Science) and topped off with covers by ASTONISHING X-MEN artist JOHN CASSADAY! Collecting S.W.O.R.D. #1-5
name: TPB

volume.name: X-Men: S.W.O.R.D. - No Time To Breathe

description: Can life be any better for Takeya? He's surrounded by three beautiful women: Ren, Myu and Neneko. Unfortunately, some things can be too good to last when a DearS agent arrives to take Ren away as a defective slave. She will have to learn free will if she truly wishes to demonstrate to the rest of the DearS community that she really wants to stay with her new master.
name: Vol. 2

description: After Ren battles a DearS Biter attempting to recapture her and Takeya asserts his rights as Ren's owner in order to save her from termination, their lives are further complicated by the arrival of Takeya's little sister Natsuki. Due to her fangirlish worship of the alien DearS, Natsuki initially declares herself Ren's bosom friend, but she changes her tune once she hears Ren declare herself Takeya's slave -- Ren is suddenly a perverted, impure alien and a living symbol of the DearS' plot to corrupt and take over the entire planet.
name: Vol. 3

description: FALL OF THE HULKS continues in this action-packed story! What secrets will be revealed? What plans has the RED HULK been hiding from everyone? And what does all of this have to do with the COSMIC HULK robot!? Dont miss this thrilling tale by JEFF PARKER (Agents of Atlas, The Hood) and CARLOS RODRIGUES (Thunderbolts)! Collecting FALL OF THE HULKS: RED HULK #1-4 and material from INCREDIBLE HULK #606-608
name: Fall of the Hulks: Red Hulk (Trade Paperback)

volume.name: Fall of the Hulks: Red Hulk

description: Meet Nia. Her trainer Xaki is teaching her to be a Biter. She looks up to her trainer, and will do anything for him, including tracking down some Zero Number named Ren! When word gets out that Ren escaped from Xaki when he tried to bring her back to the community, Nia sets out to avenge the dishonor done to her trainer. Meanwhile, Ren is getting more attention from class playboy Hiro, who tries to plant doubt in her mind about the nature of her relationship with her "master." And when Rubi, a DearS dominatrix, begins to mark her territory, could Ren be headed for the recycling bin?
name: Vol. 4

description: When Takeya rescues Ren from DearS dominatrix Barker Rubi, the trauma has caused her to lose her Japanese language skills. The cure? A little R&R, of course! They take a class trip to the resort town of Bousou, where the beach bum DearS Ayu tries to help Ren recover with a game of high-flying beach volleyball. But wait! What the heck is that weird alien creature that has fallen from the sky--and through Takeya's roof? Everyone will just have to take a chill pill, because DearS Watcher Fina, Rubi's superior, has her own plans for Ren and Takeya...
name: Vol. 5

description: The new school term has started for our heroes and between needing to help Ren get changed into her uniform and Hiro-kun still making all the moves on the oblivious alien, Takeya's plate of stress and trouble is nicely topped with a surprise visit from Miu who is desperate to return his sharp-pen to him. Ren declares her resilience to kiss no one but her Master, a lesson in Ren's innate loyalty and Miu's growing affection toward Takeya. We then get a glimpse of what the heck is up with Khi and those constant Band-Aids on his face. Acne problem? We find out that Sample a2 is in fact a child DearS.
name: Vol. 6

description: When a fun trip to the pool turns lethal, an ill-stricken Takeya must find a way to save the day. And a design convention can mean a future career for the young Neneko. But when the DearS begin to become increasingly inquisitive and potentially confused about this human thing called LOVE, it's going to take everyone in the neighborhood to sort out the mess. The disappearance of Io...the re-appearance of Nia...Takeya unwittingly becomes the Master of two Servants--all this excitement and more in the next volume of DearS!
name: Vol. 7

description: Where were we...Oh, yes--Hiro and Ren at the rabbit pen! Unfortunately for Hiro, Ren runs off to Takeya, unaware of the deep emotional connection Hiro feels for her. Up on the DearS spaceship, Fina says her job as Watcher is over! Down on Earth, Neneko shows Takeya how Io has entered some strange cocoon state...on her apartment ceiling! And when Takeya's estranged father emerges on the scene, he reveals a stunning secret about the DearS. Could Ren be the key to saving everyone?
name: Vol. 8

description: Rainier's frightening creations--amalgams of both dragon and technology--wreak carnage on Malikai, Grace and the group in the slums of San Francisco, as they attempt to escape with their lives! Along the way, an alliance will shatter, friends will become foes, and the true destructive nature of their ferocious enemies begins to take shape, with horrific implications for all beings of magic!
name: Strangers In The Night

description:
The sixth storyline in The Punisher MAX. By Garth Ennis and Goran Parlov.

Story

After taking out a gang of coke dealers Frank discovers that they are linked to a corporation and is convinced to take them down by a hostage held saved from the gangsters. However, his enemies knows that he is coming for them and hire the Barracuda to kill him.

Barracuda sees Frank coming for them and runs knocks him out when he runs down Frank's taxi with his car. Frank regains consciousness and a fight ensues. In a brutal fight The Punisher stabs Barracuda in the eye, cuts off his fingers with a hatchet and he chokes him with barb wire. Barracuda does not go down, and he eventually knocks out frank, ties him up, and throws him into the shark infested ocean. Frank escapes the sharks and makes it to shore. He then regroups and plants explosives on the boats. He detonates the bombs when Ebbing and Barracuda are both on the boat. Barracuda somehow manages to survive the explosion and swims to Frank's boat where he shoots him in the head, killing him.
name: Barracuda

description:
Seventh Volume of The Punisher MAX. By Garth Ennis and Leandro Fernanadez.

Story

When taking out a gang of drug dealers Frank learns that the Russians have a bounty on him. He then learns that Kathryn O'Brien had been captured in Afghanistan and decides to help her. Frank goes to Afghanistan and meets O'Brien. Punisher and Kathryn are then captured by Nikolai Zakharov who interrogate them on a helicopter. There they find out that Zakharov was able to find them through information he received from Rawlins. The Punisher and Kathryn break free and fight back. During the fight the helicopter crashes but Frank and Kathryn manage to use a parachute to escape before impact. On the ground Kathryn steps on a landmine and dies. Frank later finds Zakharov still alive but paralyzed from the helicopter crash and crushes his skull with a rock. Punisher then tracks down Rawlins and kills him.
name: Man Of Stone
